1973;;The Last American Hero;;American;;Lamont Johnson;;Jeff Bridges, Valerie Perrine, Ned Beatty;;biography;;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Last_American_Hero;;Junior Jackson (Jeff Bridges), a stock-car driver stays one step ahead of reform school until his father (Art Lund) is thrown in prison for moonshining. Seeing the error of his ways, Jackson begins to concentrate on his driving skills, hoping to become a professional stock car racer to raise money to get his father released from jail.[4]